FT  10 DEC 92 / UK Company News: NEI plans to cancel preference shares
Northern Engineering Industries, the Rolls-Royce sub-sidiary, is proposing
to cancel and repay its outstanding 3 per cent, 5.375 per cent and 11 per
cent preference shares.
For the 3 per cent it is offering 105p, against a mid-market price on
December 4 of 40p, giving a gross exit yield of 3.8 per cent. The 100p offer
for the 5.375 per cent, against a market price of 70p, gives a yield of 7.2
per cent.
Holders of the 11 per cent are being offered 125p, against a market price of
118p, for a yield of 11.6 per cent.
